Life is goin full force....
I move into my place this weekend.
I just bought a new car.
Still start school in Aug.
And I have a crush on a different boy..
Who's way better than the last crush. hehe
And I actually get to see this one on a semi-regular basis.. since he lives here.
And doesn't just come to Az once a week.
I am officially joining the adult ranks as of the 16th.
(hyperventilation status is about to start)
but I'm so fucking excited. Holy Good Lord!

okay.. so i start school in august. 
the wedding was fucking fantastic.
i got approved for my apartment.
i love my job.
i have a huge crush on someone.
who has a crush back.
and its totally no pressure. 
i love life.

god. it hurts my ribs to cough anymore. i just wish id stop! 
i think im gonna go smoke a bowl, and hook up my N64.. try to take my mind off being so friggin poopy. :)

so i think i might start writing in this a lil more.. wont be easy though since i have to use my roomates computer... but i was sent home sick today.. i was all worried cause im still temp, and missed a lot during feb and march due to migraines.. so i really didnt want to go. but my boss assured me that since she was sending me home, id be okay.. so i slept..and am going to sleep even more. i love my bed. 
so im quite happy right now though.. i go to cali on the 17th for the wedding, and we're going to drive home down the PCH.. so excited about that. and i applied at the apt i want yesterday.. hopefully i get it.. cause the rent is totally doable with the special they have.. but i wont move in till july.. im supposed to become permanent in june.. and i start school in aug. busy summer. lol. im taking honors english, sociology, and photography. it should be fun. but ill be going to class from 7 to 10 monday through thursday. eek. i hope im not taking on more than i should.. but i think itll be fine. i need to save up so i can go to disneyland this winter. my best friend jimi and i are wanting to go cause well, its an anniversary year, they make it snow now, AND in the wintertime, they make the haunted mansion into nightmare before christmas. omg i have to go! okay.. and i think im heading off to bed now. night. :)

Okay.. so the only thing i really have to complain about is money issues, as always... 
I applied for financial aid so i can take some classes in the fall. Then once Im done with those.. Im joining the Air National Guard. So i can travel. and have the rest of my schooling paid for. Im eating right(mostly vegetarian), excersising, working, seeing friends.. i got my bridesmaid dress yesterday, and im happy to say that it falls off me now.. since i ordered it a while ago... before the huge break up that caused me to drop 4 sizes.. i barely have time to myself.. well.. thats not true either.. i try to put time aside at the end of each night so i can read. ive read a lot lately and i miss it. i love having my time to myself, and being able to do what i want. when i want. dating here and there.... have had to tell only one guy off.. that got way too attached way too fast. im not on the lookout for a boyfriend. just people to have fun with. and maybe 1 or 2 to play with. hehe.. soooo. i want to start writing again though. thats the main thing i want to work on since ekosphere didnt work out.. i need to find a band with the same ideals as me, and id like to have some lyrics already in the bag. something to bring to the table. i still have a lot to do to get my classes, i need to test, and register.. im taking a photography class too.. english, math, and 1 elective. then off i go hopefully to see the world. cause when i join the air guard, im hoping to get on an inflight refueling air crew... so then ill get sent whereever they need me to be. :) alright.. must go to ikea... just havent written in here in a while..

I havent been on this site for quite some time now... trying to put my life back together, and im pretty optimistic.. theres been way too much shit goin on for me this year. but i finally see the light, and its time to start makin shit happen. the biggest thing for me right now, is focusing on myself, and trying out for Ekosphere. I am finally actually trying out for a band. singing has always been my dream, and now im ready to focus on it. im ready to find me. :) theres still a lot of hurt to heal from. but brad and i finally talked.. really really talked. and i let everything out. i didnt hold anything back this time. funny thing is, he already realized.. finally. now we can work on a friendship, and now that that door of communication has been opened, i only hope we can continue it. Im a different person already. seriously, life can only get better from here.. at least for me, personally. im a little concerned for the country.. cause i sure as hell didnt vote for bush, and i cant believe how divided our country is. i should just move to amsterdam.

Im better. 
Im actually quite happy. I had a change of heart all of a sudden.. something clicked. and im excited. im not gonna go into too much detail.. because its probably cheesy.. but, lets just say, im excited to see who i turn out to be. ive let myself and so many other things and people go, and i am so looking forward to recapturing myself. so yeah. i guess om doin pretty good. :)

The Ultimate Death Survey What do you think happens after you die? Havent decided that one quite yet. Do you believe in heaven? sometimes Do you believe in hell? sometimes Do you think you will be judged after you die? i hope not How many people would attend your funeral? dont know.. a few, im sure Would you rather that people cry or laugh at your funeral? whateve is going to help them get over it i guess. What's better? A shot in the head or downing pills? um.. pills. What should be written on your tombstone? i dont know. havent thought about that one. something nice about me. lol Would you rather die childless or divorced? neither.. since im not going to have to worry about either one... but if i had to pick.. id say childless. Do you want to die in the morning, afternoon, or night? whenever im asleep.. so night.. unless its during a nap.. lol If you had a million dollars to leave, who would you leave it to? i would split ip up between my living relatives.. and that special someone if i had one at the time.. What kind of flowers do you want at your funeral? gardenia, iris, magnolia, and some others that i cant think of right now. On your deathbed, which moment will you most remember? hopefully one that i have yet to make. Have you ever watched someone die? my baby... (a cat..i had her from the time i was 5 till 19.. she waited for me to come home from work.) What's the most gruesome death you can imagine? How often do you think about death? depends on my mood. lol Is fear of dying your number one fear? no Do you believe in reincarnation? sometimes Have you ever wished someone you loved were dead? once or twice Do you consider life short or long? too short Do you think you have a soul? sometimes i wonder Assisted suicide for a terminally ill person is: fine by me. id want to do it if i was suffering so bad and i was gonna die any minute anyways... stop the misery already. If you were cremated, where would you like your ashes? i dont know.. something really cool.. like being shot into space.. or putting my ashes in a mold that goes on the bottom of the sea to rebuild reefs. i saw this show.. they really do that. or scattered anywhere in alaska.. Would you choose to be immortal, if you could be? yes.. but only if i could die when i chose to.. like no one could kill me but i knew the only way.. or something to that effect. cause you know it starts sucking really bad after a while. :) Take The Ultimate Death Survey

Thinker quiz : what your results say about you


Some people have a strong preference for one style of thinking, and find some skills come more naturally than others. Other people tend to adopt different thinking styles in different situations.

This test gives you an idea of what your current thinking style or styles are. But remember - the brain is a very adaptive organ. You should be able to improve your performance in any one of these categories with practice. 		   The Renaissance ideal

The leading thinkers of the Renaissance were not just experts in their own field. The renaissance scholar was expected to master all branches of knowledge.

With his insatiable desire to know everything, Leonardo da Vinci is often held up as the ideal Renaissance man.

I will be starting my back piece by the end of summer... !!! I am SOOO excited!
I talked to Jason(Hammers' guy)last Tues.. not this week.. but last. And he said that what I want will take about 20 hours total, and he charges 50 an hour. So all I have to do is save up 200, and then go in for my outline.. :) He said that will take about 3 to 4 hours... so yeah. I am so freaking excited I can barely stand it.
I need to figure out a way to make some kind of border around my other tats on my bak.. cause where they are is perfect for what I want to do.. space-wise.. now there wont be a way to blend them into the big one.. so I have to separate them.. any ideas, please dont hesitate to let me know. But I am going to be getting wings.. and they will pretty much cover the rest of my back. It wont have any color.. except shading. well, im thinking about putting a VERY little bit of color on the bottom part.. but I dont know. But what Im gonna do is.. the top part is going to be all feathery and pretty.. just shading.. then about a quarter of the way down or so, they will start transforming.. into leathery gargoyle style wings.. with the pointed claws on the end.. and mid way.. randomly.. i will have him put feathers wafting down.. all will be great detail, and im thinking of doing like a red or something for parts of the shading on the leathery part.. It hasnt been drawn up yet.. but Im sure itll all come together nicely. :) See, I used to love the yinyang... when i was in jr high.. but now.. it doesnt appeal to me. but the thoery still does.. so this is kinda sorta like that. bsaically showing 2 sides.. and all that. i dont want to get to philosophical here, but you get the idea. :) Yah.. oh and i absolutely LOVE my new job!!! omg. kbye.
Oh yeah, and i really dont think Im gonna go to Alaska with Eric. He likes me.. a lot. I dont want to get into it here.. but yeah. It wouldnt be wise for me to go away with him for a month.

I can't believe how happy I am right now. :) I was driving to work today, and I found myself smiling because I was happy to be going. I got transferred to Human Resources and I started on Wed. And I fucking love it. I'm at the front desk, and I get to know ALLLL the dirt on everyone at work, I have full access to their files, the work isn't hard at all, and I get to take field trips!!!! Like on Thursday, I get to ride around with the courier to all the sites to retake pictures for badges. How much fun is that gonna be? And I have to go visit the sites once every 3 months to make sure they have what they need. And then whatever else comes up. I love it.
And Brad and I are doing better than EVER. ever. Life is so fucking awesome right now. :D

So, I met this really cool guy.. and we've become fast friends. Well, he is planning a trip to Alaska... for a month. He wants to camp and hunt. Live off the land. And he invited me to come along. Ok. Once in a lifetime chance here. He told me all the money I need to save is to cover bills for the month we'll be gone. Brad already gave me his ok. Of course I'll have to save way more than for the bills, I'd have to do some major shopping, and I'd want to pay for gas and food, and I'm not going to make him pay for my room.
